cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a new perspective on multi-class ensemble classification using Kalman filters, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the practical applicability of the new algorithm, which suggests that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments performed on datasets involve image classification, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the algorithm in dealing with class label noise, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
